Perfect! I found the key styling issue. Looking at lines 87-94, I can see that `.infobox-header` and `.infobox-subheader` classes have:

```css
.infobox .infobox-header,
.infobox .infobox-subheader {
        background-color: var(--wikitable-header-bg);
        color: var(--wikitable-color);
        font-family: 'Alegreya', 'Palatino', 'Georgia', serif;
        font-weight: bold;
        text-align: center;
}
```

The `font-family: 'Alegreya', 'Palatino', 'Georgia', serif;` line is what's causing table headers to show in Alegreya font.

Looking at the image the user provided, I can see that "Rosewood mast with silk sail" is the main header, "Properties" and "Values" appear to be subheaders in the table. These would be styled with `.infobox-header` and `.infobox-subheader` classes respectively.

The user wants to remove the special styling (Alegreya font) from table headers but keep it for section headers. I need to find out how section headers are styled to make sure I don't affect those.

Let me also check the base.css and fonts.css files to understand the broader font styling approach.

